    <h2 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:1.8rem;color:var(--charcoal);margin-bottom:1rem;">Planetary Mixers</h2>
<img src="/images/spiral-mixer.jpg" alt="Spiral Mixer" class="product-img" loading="lazy">

    <p style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Planetary mixers are the most versatile commercial mixer. The attachment orbits the bowl while rotating on its own axis — just like a planet around the sun, hence the name. They come with three standard attachments: a flat beater for batters and frostings, a dough hook for bread and pizza dough, and a wire whisk for creams and meringues.</p>
    <div class="card-grid" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
      <div class="card"><h3>5–7 Litre Planetary Mixer</h3>
<img src="/images/dough-mixer.jpg" alt="Dough Mixer" class="product-img" loading="lazy">
<p>Bench-top models for small bakeries, cafés, and home bakers scaling up. Handles cake batters, frostings, small dough batches.</p><div class="price-tag">₹18,000 – ₹45,000</div><p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Small bakeries, cafés, home bakers</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>10–15 Litre Planetary Mixer</h3><p>Mid-range floor-standing or bench models. The most popular size for Indian bakeries producing 50–200 items per day.</p><div class="price-tag">₹40,000 – ₹90,000</div><p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Medium bakeries, restaurants</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>20–30 Litre Planetary Mixer</h3><p>Serious commercial production. Heavy-duty construction, powerful motors (1–2 HP), and large bowl capacity for high-volume baking.</p><div class="price-tag">₹80,000 – ₹1,80,000</div><p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Large bakeries, hotel kitchens</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>40–60 Litre Planetary Mixer</h3><p>Industrial-grade planetary mixers for high-volume production. Requires floor-mounting and three-phase power supply.</p><div class="price-tag">₹1,60,000 – ₹4,00,000</div><p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Industrial bakeries, large-scale catering</p></div>
    </div>

    <h2 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:1.8rem;color:var(--charcoal);margin-bottom:1rem;">Spiral Dough Mixers</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Spiral mixers are purpose-built for bread dough. The spiral hook and rotating bowl work together to develop gluten gently and efficiently, without overheating the dough. If you bake bread, pizza dough, or roti dough in large quantities, a spiral mixer will outperform a planetary mixer every time.</p>
    <div class="card-grid" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
      <div class="card"><h3>10–20 Litre Spiral Mixer</h3><p>Entry-level spiral mixers for artisan bakeries and pizzerias. Single-speed or two-speed options.</p><div class="price-tag">₹35,000 – ₹85,000</div><p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Small artisan bakeries, pizzerias</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>30–40 Litre Spiral Mixer</h3><p>Mid-range commercial spiral mixer. Can handle 15–20 kg of dough per batch. Industry standard for medium bakeries.</p><div class="price-tag">₹80,000 – ₹1,80,000</div><p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Medium-large bakeries, bread specialists</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>60–100 Litre Spiral Mixer</h3><p>Heavy industrial spiral mixers for large-scale dough production. Some models have removable bowls for faster workflow.</p><div class="price-tag">₹1,80,000 – ₹5,00,000</div><p style="font-size:.85rem;color:var(--ink-light);margin-top:.5rem;">Best for: Industrial bakeries, large production units</p></div>
    </div>

    <h2 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:1.8rem;color:var(--charcoal);margin-bottom:1rem;">Food Processors & Cutters</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Commercial food processors save hours of prep time in restaurant kitchens. They slice, dice, shred, and purée at speeds no human can match. For Indian restaurants with complex prep requirements — think extensive vegetable cutting, masala grinding, and coconut processing — a good food processor is essential.</p>
    <div class="card-grid" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
      <div class="card"><h3>Vegetable Cutter / Slicer</h3><p>High-speed disc cutter for slicing, dicing, and shredding vegetables. Essential for high-volume restaurant kitchens.</p><div class="price-tag">₹25,000 – ₹90,000</div></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Bowl Cutter (Cutter Mixer)</h3><p>Rotating bowl with high-speed blades for emulsifying, blending, and fine-cutting. Used for minced meat, pastes, and forcemeats.</p><div class="price-tag">₹60,000 – ₹2,50,000</div></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Dough Sheeter / Laminator</h3><p>Rolls dough to consistent thickness for croissants, puff pastry, and pasta. Saves hours of manual rolling.</p><div class="price-tag">₹45,000 – ₹1,50,000</div></div>
    </div>

